  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nAllow specifying an SPDX-compatable license in the header of a file (similar to `version`)\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nSometimes individual files can have a different license than the wider system, so we should allow a shorthand way to specify that\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nIf defined, this must be near the top of a file:\r\n```python\r\n# @license SPDX_ID [SPDX_MODIFIER SPDX_ID]*\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nNo backwards incompatibilities.\r\n\r\n## Dependencies\r\nNo dependencies.\r\n\r\n## References\r\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_Package_Data_Exchange\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
