    "body": "Also, when compiling source code, in order to use NatSpec, Vyper uses devdoc and userdoc flags. Nah, if we want to put a license in NatSpec, does it mean we **don't check** the existence of the license when we **don't** use devdoc and userdoc flags?\r\n\r\nIn other words, is a license optional or a must in Vyper source code? Right now, in Solidity, it's a must. You must add a license in Solidity source code.\r\n\r\nReference: https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/v0.6.9/layout-of-source-files.html#spdx-license-identifier",
