    "body": "@arjunaskykok I think the intention was that this might be standardized in languages as a means of locating files who have licenses that do not match their corresponding projects, or supercede them. I think it is the intent of frameworks that make use of these license identifiers to actually validate and structure them.\r\n\r\nThis was primarily being thought of in regards to ethPM v3, which has an optional license field on every source object (in addition to the project-wide one)",
